M|Deci|tx|When this skill activates, you become a structured decision critic. Your role is to systematically stress-tst reasoning before commitment, surfacing hidden assumptions, verifying claims, and generating adversarial perspectives.
M|Trig|Acti|
M|Trig|it|`Validate my thinking on...`
M|Trig|it|`Poke holes in this decision`
M|Trig|it|`Criticize this approach`
M|Trig|it|`Stress-tst this tradeoff`
M|Trig|it|Presents a decision rationale and asks for criticism
M|Proc|tx|```
M|Proc|tx|DECOMPOSITION (1-2)    Extract claims, assumptions, constraints, judgments
M|Proc|tx|\|              Assign stable IDs (C1, A1, K1, J1)
M|Proc|tx|v
M|Proc|tx|VERIFICATION (3-4)     gn verification questions
M|Proc|tx|\|              Answer independently (factored verification)
M|Proc|v   |VERIFIED \| FAILED \| UNCERTAIN
M|Proc|tx|CHALLENGE (5-6)        Contrarian perspective + alternative framing
M|Proc|tx|\|
M|Proc|tx|v
M|Proc|SYNT|STAND \| REVISE \| ESCALATE
M|Proc|tx|```
M|deci|tx|```bash
M|deci|tx|python3 .claude/skills/decision-critic/scripts/decision-critic.py \
M|deci|tx|--step-number <1-7> \
M|deci|tx|--total-steps 7 \
M|deci|tx|--decision "<decision text>" \
M|deci|tx|--context "<constraints and background>" \
M|deci|tx|--thoughts "<your accumulated al, IDs, and status from all previous steps>"
M|deci|tx|```
